results.name: Square array read by antidiagonals: a(n, d) is the smallest number that begins an arithmetic progression with common difference d of n numbers with the same prime signature.
comment: First two columns are A034173 and A113457. First three rows are A000012, A086489 and A113458.
example: a(3, 2) = 3 because 3, 5 and 7 have the same prime signature.
